Package: mergecalib
Type: Package
Title: Deterministic Cell Merging for Interval Calibration Targets
Version: 0.2.0.9000
Authors@R: person(given = "Kunxiang", family = "Ma", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "makunxiangiphone@icloud.com")
Description: Builds deterministic within-province cell-merging plans for
    demographic cell data. Final merged cells are constrained to have positive
    sample size. Provincial and national subgroup proportions for multiple
    outcome grades can be required to fall inside user-supplied intervals.
    Candidate clusters are selected with a set-partitioning mixed-integer
    linear program, followed by lexicographic minimization of merged sample
    size, demographic distance, outcome heterogeneity, weight distortion, and
    merge count. Structural infeasibility and the minimum uniform target-range
    relaxation are reported explicitly.
